    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Closing this; I've thought about it for a long time and I just don't think it's a good idea. There's no harm to having an empty file be generated; applications can simply not use it. [Also the file might not be empty forever.](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/3898)\r\n\r\nIt's somewhat analogous to the API design decision of \"if you write a function that returns a list of results, and a particular call of the function has no results, return an empty list rather than returning `null` and creating special cases for your users \"."
  }
